To target both the Islamic and Chinese markets, new IT-based start-ups should perform extensive market research and modify their goods and services to fit the distinct demands and preferences of each market. Cultural sensitivity and language localisation are two critical factors to consider. It is critical to understand and respect the Muslim market's cultural and religious values, while also ensuring that all materials and communications are translated and presented in a manner that Chinese customers can comprehend. Building partnerships and collaborations with local firms and influencers may also help you reach and engage these target consumers. 